0. Flattened domain model - one class with all parameters.
1. Import BeerXML data from local file - parse it to java objects.
2. Save data to database - data only necessary for statistics.
3. Get data from db and present it in form of statistics (REST):
    - average gravity;
    - average alcohol;
    - percentage and amount of light/amber/dark beers;
    - beers/year;
    - favorite style (general styles);
    - amount brewed.
4. Angular front.
5. Import BeerXML data from uploaded file.
6. Validation
7. Tests